quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  49,1,"O you who believe! Do not push yourself forward in the presence of Allah and his Messenger, and fear Allah. Allah does indeed hear all, know all"
  49,2,"O you who believe! Raise not your voices above the Prophet's voice, nor speak loudly to him as you speak loudly to one another, lest your deeds become unwittingly worthless"
  49,3,Those indeed who lower their voices before Allah's Messenger — they are those whose minds Allah has tested for piety. For them there is forgiveness and a great reward
  49,4,"Those indeed who call out to you [Prophet] from outside the private chambers — most of them have no sense"
  49,5,"And had they been patient till you [Muhammad] come out to them, it would have been better for them. And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  49,6,"O you who believe! Should a depraved person bring you news, examine it critically, lest you harm a people in ignorance, and then be sorry for what you did"
  49,7,"And beware! Allah's Messenger is amongst you. Were he to obey you in most matters, you would surely be in trouble. But Allah has endeared the faith to you and has made it seem good in your minds. And He has made hateful to you suppression of the Truth and transgression and disobedience. Those are the ones rightly guided"
  49,8,"A favour from Allah and a bounty! And Allah is Omniscient, Wise"
  49,9,"And if two parties of the believers quarrel, make peace between them. Then if one of them does wrong to the other, fight that one which does wrong, till it returns to Allah's command. Then, if it returns, make peace between them with justice and act equitably. Allah does indeed love those that are equitable"
  49,10,The believers are but brethren. So make peace among your brothers! And fear Allah so that mercy is showered upon you